 277:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** /** @defgroup FLASHEx_Exported_Functions_Group2 Option Bytes Programming functions
 278:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****  *  @brief   Option Bytes Programming functions
 279:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****  *
 280:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** @verbatim   
 281:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   ==============================================================================
 282:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****                 ##### Option Bytes Programming functions ##### 
 283:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   ==============================================================================  
 284:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
 285:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     [..] Any operation of erase or program should follow these steps:
 286:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) Call the HAL_FLASH_OB_Unlock() function to enable the Flash option control 
 287:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         register access.
 288:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) Call following function to program the desired option bytes.
 289:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_FLASHEx_OBProgram:
 290:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****          - To Enable/Disable the desired sector write protection.
 291:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****          - To set the desired read Protection Level.
 292:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****          - To configure the user option Bytes: IWDG, STOP and the Standby.
 293:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****          - To Set the BOR level.
 294:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) Once all needed option bytes to be programmed are correctly written, call the
 295:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         HAL_FLASH_OB_Launch(void) function to launch the Option Bytes programming process.
 296:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) Call the HAL_FLASH_OB_Lock() to disable the Flash option control register access (recommend
 297:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         to protect the option Bytes against possible unwanted operations).
 298:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
 299:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     [..] Proprietary code Read Out Protection (PcROP):
 300:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) The PcROP sector is selected by using the same option bytes as the Write
 301:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         protection (nWRPi bits). As a result, these 2 options are exclusive each other.
 302:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) In order to activate the PcROP (change the function of the nWRPi option bits), 
 303:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         the WPRMOD option bit must be activated.
 304:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) The active value of nWRPi bits is inverted when PCROP mode is active, this
 305:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         means: if WPRMOD = 1 and nWRPi = 1 (default value), then the user sector "i"
 306:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         is read/write protected.
 307:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****     (#) To activate PCROP mode for Flash sector(s), you need to call the following function:
 308:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_FLASHEx_AdvOBProgram in selecting sectors to be read/write protected
 309:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_FLASHEx_OB_SelectPCROP to enable the read/write protection
 310:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
 311:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** @endverbatim
 312:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   * @{
 313:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   */
 314:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** 
 315:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_flash_ex.c **** /**
